blence with the commander in Forbidden Planet.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 1 2010, 08:26:34 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://paulwoodlin.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"paulwoodlin","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"paulwoodlin","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://paulwoodlin.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"paulwoodlin","ctime_ts":1291191994,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416528#t11416528","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416528#t11416528","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416528#t11416528","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"solanocard","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11416528,"talkid":44595,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416528#t11416528","upictitle":"solanocard: pic#0","article":"It could... but then we'd have to upgrade to a rule of 4.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 1 2010, 19:25:46 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Rule of 3","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"solanocard","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"solanocard","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"solanocard","ctime_ts":1291231546,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416784#t11416784","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416784#t11416784","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416784#t11416784","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"solanocard","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11416784,"talkid":44596,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11416784#t11416784","upictitle":"solanocard: pic#0","article":"reread what I wrote, \"the BEST of the 3 Star Wars movies\" that is one movie. I was referencing that the best movie in the original trilogy was directed by Kershner, not that the original trilogy was directed by Kershner.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 1 2010, 19:27:38 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Rule of 3","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"solanocard","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"solanocard","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://solanocard.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"solanocard","ctime_ts":1291231658,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11418064#t11418064","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11418064#t11418064","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11418064#t11418064","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ashley_falls","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://ashley-falls.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11418064,"talkid":44601,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11418064#t11418064","upictitle":"ashley_falls: pic#0","article":"I really need to go back and check out Leslie's films from the 50's and 60's. I wonder if my perception of him as one of the goofiest comedic actors will retroactively imbue his early \"serious\" work with an element of farce. Personally, I'll always regard \"The Naked Gun\" movies as the high point of the brand of farce that \"Airplane\" started (although the presence of OJ Simpson does make the films a little creepy). Those four films are pretty much bear the gold standard of a genre that's been saturated so much it's as dead as Mr. Nielsen.\n\nThe most wonderful thing about his gifts as an artist was probably the way, he played comedy completely straight. He could say a line like, \"Come in, Jimmy. Sit down. Let's have a talk.\" with total sincerity and somehow it would be funny, despite the total lack of any discernible joke. Somehow, his very presence in a movie carried  the mythic resonance of someone who has made you laugh over and over, again. Every time he'd open his mouth, part of you wanted to laugh. Even when he was slumming it in lame fair like \"Spy Hard\", he always made me giggle.\n\nI'm sad he's gone but I'm also glad that he lived such a long life. Just the same, I can't think of a single male actor from his generation that's still alive, working and could do comedy as well as he could. Sure, Betty White and Cloris Leachman are still around and doing terrific work. But the void Leslie leaves behind is one that can never be filled.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 2 2010, 01:37:17 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Memories...","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://ashley-falls.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ashley_falls","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ashley_falls","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://ashley-falls.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"ashley_falls","ctime_ts":1291253837,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11420624#t11420624","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11420624#t11420624","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11420624#t11420624","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"davenielsen78","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://davenielsen78.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11420624,"talkid":44611,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11420624#t11420624","upictitle":"davenielsen78: pic#0","article":"I only saw that movie after having seen all his comedies.  He was a comic genius but only an average \"serious\" actor, great as Forbidden Planet was.  Had he never done a comedy he probably wouldn't be known outside of Science Fiction fans.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 2 2010, 22:53:27 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://davenielsen78.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"davenielsen78","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"davenielsen78","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://davenielsen78.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"davenielsen78","ctime_ts":1291330407,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/106397433/32585154","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424208#t11424208","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424208#t11424208","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424208#t11424208","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_345626","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/cyndiebeth","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11424208,"talkid":44625,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424208#t11424208","upictitle":"Cyndie Wolf Brummer: pic#106397433","article":"George, My uncle was Bobby Strydio (mom is Sis).  Wanted to reach out and let you know that Uncle Bobby passed away this past spring. We are so glad to know that someone from their old neighborhood has had such amazing success.  I just started the series, reading Game of Thrones.  Great stuff!  Cyndie ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 4 2010, 13:36:00 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Bobby Strydio","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/cyndiebeth","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Cyndie Wolf Brummer","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_345626","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=32585154&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Cyndie Wolf Brummer","ctime_ts":1291469760,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424976#t11424976","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424976#t11424976","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424976#t11424976","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":11424976,"talkid":44628,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/186320.html?thread=11424976#t11424976","above":11424208,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"Please give my condolences to your mother, and any other family that Bobby may have left behind.<br /><br />I don't think I'd seen or heard from Bobby since, oh, 1966 or thereabouts, and I had no idea where he was or what had become of him... but back in the 50s, when we were both kids living two doors apart in the projects, Bobby Strydio was my best friend.  Also one of my first \"readers,\" when I used to make up monster stories and sell them to the other kids in the building for a nickle (enough to buy a candy bar or half a comic book), complete with dramatic reading.  Ever see the movie STAND BY ME?  That struck quite a chord with me.  Your uncle Bobby was the River Phoenix character, and I was Will Wheaton.  <br /><br />I am saddened to hear that he has passed away, but thanks for letting me know.  I hope he had a good life.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"December 4 2010, 18:16:27 UTC","parent":11424208,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Bobby Strydio","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1291486587,"tracked":0}]}